scripts.comment: The Vigenere cipher is a substitution cipher similar to the Caesar cipher. However, this cipher uses multiple keys to shift each letter by a different amount (repeated for the length of the message). Edit the custom block on the left to view the problem!
A couple examples using the block are shown below!

The scripts below use the block as part of an encrypted texting app! First, duplicate this role (under the "Room" tab) and invite yourself (in a new browser window) or a friend to the role. Then run the first script to send encrypted messages! Don't forget to use the same key for each role!

The Vigenere cipher is a substitution cipher similar to the Caesar cipher. However, this cipher uses multiple keys to shift each letter by a different amount (repeated for the length of the message).
Edit the custom block on the left to view the problem!
<comment collabId="item_74" x="222" y="299.8333333333333" w="90" collapsed="false">add comment here...</comment>
A couple examples using the block are shown below!

<script><block collabId="item_81" s="reportEquals"><custom-block collabId="item_81_1" s="encrypt %txt with %l"><l>cbacba</l><block collabId="item_81_2" s="reportNewList"><list><l>1</l><l>2</l><l>3</l></list></block></custom-block><l>dddddd</l></block></script>
